cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is about semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the architecture and training of the model, which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep supervision, which is a technique commonly used in neural network architectures, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of ResNets, which are a type of neural network architecture, suggesting that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its model on the CamVid dataset, which is a dataset commonly used for semantic segmentation tasks, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
